=Status=

Jorge Zapico:

"The London hackathon was the first one after the Stockholm one, and it was a success. London has a big community both of developers and of climate change, and this event brought together many of the people working on the connections of both, it was full of interesting people. I was happy to see the idea taking its own life.

There were sixteen projects presented, my personal favorite was one tonne, a site were you can budget one ton of co2 to different lifestyles choices.
(http://www.sustainableinternet.org/2012/london-green-hackathon/


